        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:02PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Hays, or 16 miles north of Zortman, moving northeast
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hays and Lodge Pole.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
